text: India’s Gukesh Dommaraju, 18, defeated China’s Ding Liren, 32, at the FIDE World Chess Championship held at the Resorts World Sentosa in Singapore on Dec. 12. The final match was expected to go into a tiebreaker, but a blunder by Ding under pressure secured Gukesh’s victory. “I was totally in shock when I made a blunder—[Gukesh’s] facial expression shows that he was very excited and happy,” said Ding. Gukesh is now the youngest world chess champion, shattering the record held by Garry Kasparov, who was 22 when he won in 1985. The total prize fund for the competition was US$2.5 million (S$3.3 million), of which the champion took home around US$1.35 million (S$1.8 million). #fyp #chess #chesstok #news
